article.description: Chris Davenport scored 18 points and Trent Mackey 15 as North Florida broke away early to defeat Austin Peay 80-70 Wednesday night.
article.headline: Davenport sparks North Florida, beats Austin Peay 80-70
article.linkText: Davenport sparks North Florida, beats Austin Peay 80-70
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. -- Chris Davenport scored 18 points and Trent Mackey 15 as North Florida broke away early to defeat Austin Peay 80-70 Wednesday night. The lead changed hands five times early -- and was tied twice -- before Davenport and Beau Beech scored baskets and Aaron Bodager added a 3-pointer, and North Florida (9-4) opened a 16-10 lead after the 7-0 run. The lead grew to 41-24 by halftime. Chris Horton scored the last six points of the game -- including back-to-back dunks -- as Austin Peay (4-7) cut the gap in the final minutes. Horton scored a career-high 28 points on 13-for-19 shooting to lead the Governors, the only one in double figures, and added 17 rebounds. North Florida made 31 of 63 shots (49 percent) and made 13 3-pointers -- the seventh straight game with 10 or more 3s. Beech scored 14 points and Dallas Moore 12 with eight assists for the Ospreys.
